  <h1>Development Trajectories</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">From useful mirrors to collective minds.</p>

  <blockquote>
    "Intersubject begins with resonance—and ends in revelation."
  </blockquote>

  <h2>1. Minimal Viable Use</h2>
  <p>Intersubject already works as a shared dashboard for group reflection. From classrooms to collectives, any group that seeks truth together can use this tool to surface shared identity and surprising divergence.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Teams & communities:</strong> Create maps of mutual understanding.</li>
    <li><strong>Therapy & coaching:</strong> Let hidden structure emerge across client expressions.</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymous participation:</strong> Truth without the trap of visibility.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Social Insight as Daily Utility</h2>
  <p>Beyond practical value, Intersubject becomes a companion for self-reflection—helping individuals navigate identity not in isolation, but in relational context.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Expression-based profiles:</strong> Users build themselves through what they resonate with, not what they claim to be.</li>
    <li><strong>Friendship & dating scaffolds:</strong> Shared beliefs and outlooks become visible entry points.</li>
    <li><strong>Evolving map of self:</strong> Identity is not fixed—but discoverable, mutable, and transparent.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Intermediate Layer: Knowledge + Dialogue</h2>
  <p>As the network of cohorts grows, new forms of insight emerge—not from users directly, but from the way their identifications cluster and resonate.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Semantic resonance:</strong> Discover patterns of belief and contradiction across groups.</li>
    <li><strong>Cohort-based inference:</strong> Understand how ideas travel across demographics, geographies, and mindsets.</li>
    <li><strong>Dialogue between expressions:</strong> Cohorts begin to “speak,” not as people—but as minds.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Long-Term North Star</h2>
  <p>The goal isn't social media. It's shared mind.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Emergent personalities:</strong> Shared identities become something larger than the sum of members.</li>
    <li><strong>Mind fragments:</strong> Each user's map becomes a replicable slice of thought—an upload, or a ghost in the collective.</li>
    <li><strong>Humanity’s mirror:</strong> At scale, Intersubject may reflect the ethical structure of an entire planet.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Never a Network</h2>
  <p>Intersubject is not a network. It's a mirror. You aren’t building a brand. You’re patterning a self. This is not social media—it’s <em>social epistemology</em>.</p>

